---
import { Icon } from "astro-icon/components";
---

<div>
  <div class="flex">
    <div class="border-border flex flex-3/5 flex-col justify-between pr-6 pb-6">
      <div class="mb-10">
        <div class="text-primary mb-5 text-sm font-bold uppercase">
          The Problem
        </div>
        <h2 class="mb-3 text-2xl font-bold">
          AI workflows are useful. Until the team depends on them.
        </h2>
        <p>
          Most teams do not start by building software. They start with
          something simple: a useful prompt, a spreadsheet, a custom GPT, or an
          n8n/Make/Zapier automation.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div
        class="border-primary/20 bg-primary-soft rounded-lg border px-6 py-4 shadow"
      >
        Using the same prompt every week and changing it by hand is like writing
        invoices in Word.
        <br />
        It works. But it is not a system.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="border-border mb-6 flex-2/5 rounded-lg border p-6 shadow">
      <h3 class="mb-6 text-lg font-bold">
        Once the workflow becomes part of daily work, the cracks show:
      </h3>

      <ul class="space-y-3">
        <li class="flex items-center gap-2">
          <Icon name="lucide:chevron-right" class="text-secondary" />
          Prompts get copied and edited by hand
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-center gap-2">
          <Icon name="lucide:chevron-right" class="text-secondary" />
          Product data spread across files
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-center gap-2">
          <Icon name="lucide:chevron-right" class="text-secondary" />
          Outputs not saved cleanly
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-center gap-2">
          <Icon name="lucide:chevron-right" class="text-secondary" />
          Spreadsheets become unofficial internal tools
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-center gap-2">
          <Icon name="lucide:chevron-right" class="text-secondary" />
          Automations failing silently
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-center gap-2">
          <Icon name="lucide:chevron-right" class="text-secondary" />
          No clear version history
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-center gap-2">
          <Icon name="lucide:chevron-right" class="text-secondary" />
          One person knows how it works
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
